<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>Should You Outsource Your Morning Routine to a Chatbot?</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/magazine/ai-chatbot-morning-routine-videos.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/magazine/ai-chatbot-morning-routine-videos.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/magazine/ai-chatbot-morning-routine-videos.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A.I. wants to help you start the day. Its suggestions? Drink coffee and get dressed.</description><dc:creator>Sophie Haigney</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 09:03:39 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Habits and Routines</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">TikTok</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/14/magazine/14mag-screenland/14mag-screenland-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Aniyah Uniquee/@Aniyahuniquee